13 (j) Nothing in this rule prohibits an investigator from:
14 (A) Referencing the complaint statement or any reports or investigative notes, files, re-
15 cords or other information in the draft or final investigative report; or
16 (B) Sharing information with witnesses or individuals interviewed during the course of
17 the investigation.
18 (k) A participating impacted party may withdraw their allegations at any time prior to
19 the investigative report being finalized. The Legislative Equity Officer shall make a deter-
