21 under this paragraph after the report has been delivered to the appointing authority but no later
22 than seven days after the imposition of remedial measures under this subsection, except that any
23 appeal must be based only on:
24 (i) Newly discovered evidence that was not taken into account by the investigator;
25 (ii) A claim of process error that is being asserted by the appellant; or
26 (iii) A claim that the investigator or the person or committee that imposed a remedial measure
27 acted with bias.
28 (C) The appeal may be made to the Joint Committee on Conduct.
